it.emarolab.scene_identification_tracking.semanticSceneLibrary.tracker

Class Tracker.Item<S,I,P>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - the shape tag identifier type.
    I - the object unique identifier type.
    P - the primitive semantic object type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Semantics.Logger

    Tracker.ShapeItem
    Enclosing interface:
    Tracker<P,T extends Tracker.Item<?,?,P>>

    public abstract static class Tracker.Item<S,I,P>
extends Semantics.Base
    The base item that defines the elements of the tracking set, managed by a Tracker.

    This class defines a structure thant contains:

    • 'S': the description of the Shape. Good practice is to use an identifing tag (e.g.: an Integer) and base the shape definition it through class hierarchy, see Semantics.Primitive). fon an example.
      • getShape()
    • 'I': the unique identifier for the object to which assign a tracked shape estimation. This is a crucial point for the managing of the tracked set (see: Tracker). Good practice is to set id equal to the semantic individual that describes the object, see: Semantics.Descriptor#getIndividual().
      • getId()
    • 'P': the shape definition, and relate coefficient, of the object as a primitive representation. It describes semantically the object to be tracked in shape and it is suppose to come from perception and affected by noise.
      • getSemanticObject()

    This class gives the basic implementation by leaving to the extendings the role to implement:

    • the initialisation of the shape identifying instances: S shape;
    • the initialisation of the shape identifying instances: I id;
    • the initialisation of the shape identifying instances: P object;
    • a copy() procedure though copy constrcutors #Item(Item).
    • a shapeAs(Object) method for deciding if Semantics.WritingState.UPDATED or Tracker.UpdatingState.AVERAGED during tracking.
    • an update(Object) method to decide if the incoming belief of the shape of the object should be UPDATED, AVERAGED or Semantics.MappingState.NOT_CHANGED with the new incoming primitive semantic object.
    Nevertheless, it implement felicitating procedure for tracking set management by overwriting the equals(Object) in order to compare between each other: Tracker.Item, semantic objects ('P') and item ID ('I').
    REMARK: only this.equals( something) will work as expected, something.equals( this) not!
